#. type: Title =
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cropping a photo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:7
msgid ""
"![image](images/Tool-Crop-en.png) Often you want to crop a photo to remove "
"unwanted areas or to focus attention on the main subject. You use the "
"**Crop** tool for this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:11
msgid ""
"Unlike other tools, the crop tool is special. It is always applied to your "
"entire photo and is not placed into the [tool stack](Tool_Stack.html)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "To crop your photo:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:16
msgid "![image](images/Button-Crop.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.  Click the crop tool button in the [tool bar](Tools-Controls.html).\n"
"    (A white crop rectangle and grid will appear over your photo and the\n"
"    crop tool's controls will appear to the right of the tool bar.)\n"
"2.  If you want to constrain your photo to an aspect ratio, click the\n"
"    Constrain ratio button so that it shows a locked lock. Then, you can\n"
"    select the aspect ratio in one of two ways:\n"
"    1.  If you want a common aspect ratio, e.g., 3&nbsp;x&nbsp;5, you can\n"
"        select it from the Common Ratios menu.\n"
"    2.  If you want a custom aspect ratio, you can enter your own width\n"
"        and height into the two text fields.\n"
msgstr ""
"1.  Click the crop tool button in the [tool bar](Tools-Controls.html).\n"
"    (A white crop rectangle and grid will appear over your photo and the\n"
"    crop tool's controls will appear to the right of the tool bar.)\n"
"2.  If you want to constrain your photo to an aspect ratio, click the\n"
"    Constrain ratio button so that it shows a locked lock. Then, you can\n"
"    select the aspect ratio in one of two ways:\n"
"    1.  If you want a common aspect ratio, e.g., 3&nbsp;x&nbsp;5, you can\n"
"        select it from the Common Ratios menu.\n"
"    2.  If you want a custom aspect ratio, you can enter your own width\n"
"        and height into the two text fields.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3.  Drag the edges or corners of the white crop rectangle to where you\n"
"    want them.\n"
"4.  If you want to move the entire rectangle, you can click inside of\n"
"    it, then drag it.\n"
"5.  Optionally, you can also rotate your photo to align it. To do so:\n"
"    1.  Move the mouse outside of the crop rectangle. (The mouse will\n"
"        change to a rotate icon.)\n"
"    2.  Click and drag the mouse in the direction you want to rotate\n"
"        your photo.\n"
msgstr ""
"3.  Drag the edges or corners of the white crop rectangle to where you\n"
"    want them.\n"
"4.  If you want to move the entire rectangle, you can click inside of\n"
"    it, then drag it.\n"
"5.  Optionally, you can also rotate your photo to align it. To do so:\n"
"    1.  Move the mouse outside of the crop rectangle. (The mouse will\n"
"        change to a rotate icon.)\n"
"    2.  Click and drag the mouse in the direction you want to rotate\n"
"        your photo.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '6.  '
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:41
msgid ""
"Click the arrow button to commit the crop. (The white crop rectangle and the "
"crop tool's controls will disappear and your photo will be cropped.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Crop.markdown.txt:44
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** If you want to start over, you can click the Reset button in\n"
"the crop tool.\n"
msgstr ""

